    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-14T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="655"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7721</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Delegate to the Inter-Allied Council</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_COT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d655fn2">In full,
                                <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_578">p.
                            578</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-14T10:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. For Secretary of the Treasury:</p>
                <p>Roumanian Minister here explains the failure of his Government to give powers to
                    any representative for signing obligations due to factional jealousies in Jassy.
                    Difficulty at last overcome to this extent that the Minister at Paris is now
                    expecting to go to America soon.<note n="3" xml:id="d655fn3">Doctor <persName
                            corresp="#p_AC1">Angelescu</persName> presented his credentials as Envoy
                        Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary, Jan. 15, 1918.</note> I shall
                    see him next week. Meanwhile Minister here states that nothing can be done until
                    further developments in the Russian situation. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_COT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Crosby</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
